        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When people start looking for a solitaire ring, the focus is usually on the diamond -  the shape, size, or sparkle. But the setting around the diamond can completely change how the ring looks. One of the most popular upgrades people consider today is the halo setting.</p><p>A halo setting surrounds the centre diamond with smaller diamonds, which makes the ring look brighter and sometimes even bigger. Over time, this style has evolved into two main types: classic halo and hidden halo.</p><p>Both styles are beautiful, but they create very different effects. If you’re choosing between them or wondering whether it’s worth upgrading your solitaire ring to a halo design, understanding the differences can help you make a better decision.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Classic Halo Setting and Why It Makes the Diamond Look Bigger",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Classic Halo Setting and Why It Makes the Diamond Look Bigger</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what-is",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_EhtmDj": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Is_a_Classic_Halo_Setting_and_Why_It_Makes_the_Diamond_Look_Bigger.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Rich Text ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A classic halo setting is easy to recognize. Small diamonds are placed around the centre stone, forming a circle or “halo” that surrounds it.</p><p>This design has been popular for years because it creates a striking visual effect. The smaller diamonds reflect extra light around the main stone, which enhances sparkle.</p><p>Another reason people love halo rings is that they make the centre diamond appear larger. The halo creates a frame around the stone, giving the illusion of more size and brilliance.</p><p>Classic halo rings are often chosen for engagement rings because they have a bold and glamorous look.</p><h3>When a Classic Halo Works Best</h3><p>A classic halo setting is usually a good choice if you:<br/><br/>1.]Want maximum sparkle<br/>2.] Prefer statement jewellery<br/>3.] Want the center diamond to appear larger<br/>4.] Like traditional engagement ring styles<br/><br/>Because the halo sits on top around the centre diamond, it’s always visible from above. That’s what gives the ring its dramatic appearance.</p>",
            "custom_id": "color",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bqTWcM": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Hidden Halo and Why Many Modern Rings Use This Design",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Hidden Halo and Why Many Modern Rings Use This Design</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what-is-a",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_ytCT7h": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Is_a_Hidden_Halo_and_Why_Many_Modern_Rings_Use_This_Design.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Rich Text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A hidden halo is a newer variation of the halo setting. Instead of surrounding the diamond from the top, the small diamonds are placed under the center stone, around the base of the setting.</p><p>From the top view, the ring still looks like a classic solitaire. But when you look at it from the side, the hidden halo becomes visible and adds extra sparkle.</p><p>Many people prefer hidden halos because they add detail without making the ring look too busy.</p><h3>Why Hidden Halos Have Become So Popular</h3><p>Hidden halo settings offer a balance between simplicity and luxury. They keep the clean look of a solitaire ring while adding a subtle sparkle from underneath.</p><p>This style is often chosen by people who want something unique but still elegant.</p><p>Hidden halos also work well with modern ring designs because they add depth and dimension without overpowering the main diamond.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Simple Comparison Between Hidden Halo and Classic Halo Rings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>A Simple Comparison Between Hidden Halo and Classic Halo Rings</h2><p>Both styles are beautiful, but they create different visual effects. Here’s an easy comparison.</p>",
            "custom_id": "a-simple",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
